6	//! Future type that bridges CUDA stream callbacks with Rust's async executor.
7	//!
8	//! [`DeviceFuture`] wraps a [`DeviceOperation`] and drives it through a
9	//! three-state machine:
10	//!
11	//! ```text
12	//!   Idle ──poll()──> Executing ──callback fires──> Complete
13	//!                       │                              │
14	//!                  (enqueue work                  (return result)
15	//!                   + host callback)
16	//! ```
17	//!
18	//! On the first poll the operation is executed on its assigned stream and a
19	//! host callback is registered via `cuLaunchHostFunc`. When the GPU reaches
20	//! the callback, it wakes the future through an [`AtomicWaker`], avoiding
21	//! busy-waits.
22	//!
23	//! [`DeviceOperation`]: crate::device_operation::DeviceOperation
24	//! [`AtomicWaker`]: futures::task::AtomicWaker
