168	    /// not been handed to the caller.
169	    ///
170	    /// `result` is only populated by a successful [`execute`], so a stored
171	    /// result implies submitted GPU work. The state check excludes futures
172	    /// that never submitted anything (`Idle`, `Failed`); a `Complete` future
173	    /// can still hold a result when callback registration failed after a
174	    /// successful launch.
175	    ///
176	    /// [`execute`]: Self::execute
